// =============================================================================
// PROTOCOL CONSTANTS — mirrors protocol.py TIERS dict 1:1
// =============================================================================
// Universal chip threshold: any UTXO at or above 546 sats (Bitcoin dust
// limit) can buy into ANY tier. Per-tier thresholds were dropped per
// ) so the
// player isn't gated by chip size — only by the cost of the bet itself
// (the network fee). The reward gradient (iron 100 → gold 200k smallest
// units) still differentiates tiers; just the entry barrier is flat.
// Minimum chip size — must cover the v2 LUCKYPROTOCOL BET tx's FOUR outputs:
// vout 0 — 546 sat dust to self (the win UTXO that receives mint)
// vout 1 — 546 sat dust to PROJECT_FEE_ADDRESS (protocol fee)
// vout 2 — OP_RETURN (0 sat)
// vout 3 — drain_to(self) change (must be ≥ 546 dust threshold or
// bdk absorbs it into the miner fee + drops the output)
// Plus the miner fee on a 4-output P2WPKH tx (~300-700 sat at typical
// mainnet fee rates 1-3 sat/vB).
// Conservative floor: 546 + 546 + 700 (worst-case fee) + 546 (change
// dust) + safety margin = 2,500 sat. Below this, tx_builder.finish()
// fails with CoinSelection(InsufficientFunds), which the user can't
// easily diagnose — the UI shows a confusing "no UTXO meets threshold"
// + the broadcast fails inside bdk.
// Was 1,500 in v1 (3-output layout, no protocol fee); bumped to 2,500
// when v2 added the project-fee output.
const MIN_CHIP_SATS = 2500;

// =============================================================================
// Centralized UTXO eligibility — single source of truth.
// =============================================================================
// Three places in the UI list "the user's playable chips":
// 1. Dashboard GameCard — "X eligible UTXOs" badge under each MINE button
// 2. Game-room BUY-IN UTXO chip strip — the radial chip rack
// 3. ALMANAC DIRECT BET chip selectors (one per tier)
// And one place lists "every BTC UTXO":
// 4. UTXO screen — SELECT ALL BTC checkbox
// Previously each callsite redeclared its own.filter(...) inline. A subtle
// drift between any two predicates (forgot the `!u.token` clause, treated
// undefined `confirmations` differently, etc.) would surface as the user
// seeing different counts in different screens for the same wallet — exactly
// the bug reported in 2026-05 ("UTXO 12 / Dashboard 10 / Room 11").
// The two helpers below are the canonical predicates. The DOM render and the
// count badge use the SAME function, so they can never disagree.
// - confirmedBtcUtxos: confirmed, non-token. UTXO screen total.
// - eligibleChipUtxos: confirmed, non-token, ≥ tier threshold. Playable.
// =============================================================================
function confirmedBtcUtxos(utxos) {
  return (utxos ?? []).filter((u) => !u.token && (u.confirmations ?? 1) >= 1);
}
function eligibleChipUtxos(utxos, tier) {
  return confirmedBtcUtxos(utxos)
    .filter((u) => u.sats >= tier.threshold)
    .sort((a, b) => a.sats - b.sats);
}
